Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper involves visualizing EMA data in real-time, which involves processing and analyzing visual data. 
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper may involve natural language processing techniques for analyzing and interpreting the EMA data. 
3. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper may involve analyzing and processing sound data in conjunction with the EMA data. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper involves the use of multilinear subspace learning for creating anatomically accurate tongue and palate models. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper may involve designing and evaluating a user interface for providing visual feedback of the articulatory data.
